  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/2918 added support for retries and timeouts in Anvil, but these features don't seem to be available in Forge when fork testing, e.g. when using the [`createSelectFork`](https://book.getfoundry.sh/cheatcodes/create-select-fork) cheat.\r\n\r\nIt should ideally be possible to specify the number of retries and the timeout via the CLI or `foundry.toml`.\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nAlchemy's docs on retries: https://docs.alchemy.com/reference/throughput#retries.",
